This paper is likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category as it presents an alternative approach to implementing boosted trees, which is a popular machine learning algorithm. Additionally, the paper discusses the performance of two state-of-the-art implementations of boosted trees, XGBoost and LightGBM, which are commonly used in machine learning. 

The paper also involves data sampling techniques, which are commonly used in data science (cs.DS) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) to improve model performance. 

Furthermore, the paper presents experimental results on image classification (cs.CV), which suggests that the proposed approach may be useful for computer vision applications. 

Finally, the paper involves analysis of early stopping, which is a common technique in optimization and machine learning (cs.DM).
